messages.message:
Feedback on search - I ran a query to pull information on "Instabase Vulnerabilities SLAs" > When clicking on the source of the results, I found that it was pulling from 'deprecated' documents.

Is there a way to refine the logic to exclude deprecated sources or explicitly indicate when a result comes from a deprecated document? This would help ensure more relevant and reliable search results. :)

Thanks for your feedback @madison.c! Our team is actively looking into this issue

cc: @jayasooryan
Thank you Balaram - no rush on my end - just thought it may be good feedback to share :)
